{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01UK8rbcJAXv8nzkNcemTHT4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01RBSrr7miCAp9MTnKpznKWC","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Session 67 retrospective","prompt":"Run a session retrospective for the codeharness project.\n\nSprint status: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml\nSession issues log: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md\nCost report: Run `codeharness stats --save` to generate the cost report, then read `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/cost-report.md`.\n\nKEY CONTEXT: This is session 67. The sprint has been COMPLETE (74/74 stories, 17/17 epics done) for over 50 sessions. Ralph keeps corrupting sprint-state.json by overwriting 16-5/6/7/8 back to `review` from its stale in-memory state. Each session wastes tokens fixing the same corruption. This is the 51st occurrence.\n\nProduce a retrospective that covers:\n1. **Session summary** — no-op session, only fixed state corruption (51st time)\n2. **Issues analysis** — the ONLY issue is Ralph's stale-state overwrite loop. 51 sessions of wasted compute.\n3. **Cost analysis** — run `codeharness stats --save` and read the cost report. Focus on waste from these no-op sessions.\n4. **What went well** — sprint IS complete, all 74 stories done\n5. **What went wrong** — Ralph won't stop, state corruption persists\n6. **Lessons learned** — need sprint-complete exit condition in Ralph\n7. **Action items** — Stop Ralph. Add exit condition. Fix stale-state overwrite.\n\nIf a session retro for today already exists at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-28.md, APPEND to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,