ence.\n\nProduce a retrospective that covers:\n1. **Session summary** — no-op session, only fixed state corruption (51st time)\n2. **Issues analysis** — the ONLY issue is Ralph's stale-state overwrite loop. 51 sessions of wasted compute.\n3. **Cost analysis** — run `codeharness stats --save` and read the cost report. Focus on waste from these no-op sessions.\n4. **What went well** — sprint IS complete, all 74 stories done\n5. **What went wrong** — Ralph won't stop, state corruption persists\n6. **Lessons learned** — need sprint-complete exit condition in Ralph\n7. **Action items** — Stop Ralph. Add exit condition. Fix stale-state overwrite.\n\nIf a session retro for today already exists at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-28.md, APPEND to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","agentId":"a2620ac5f66cdb6b2","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Session 67 retrospective appended to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-28.md`.\n\nSummary:\n- **Session 67**: No-op. 51st consecutive state corruption fix. Zero productive work.\n- **Cost**: $752.05 total, up $35.20 from session 51. Estimated $112+ wasted on 51 no-op sessions. The `retro` phase alone is $82.68 (11% of total) — almost entirely from these repetitive retrospectives.\n- **Sprint**: Complete. 74/74 stories, 17/17 epics. Has been complete since session 30.\n- **Root cause**: Ralph has no sprint-complete exit condition and overwrites disk state from stale in-memory copy every loop.\n- **Action**: Stop Ralph. Add exit condition. Make `done` a terminal state. Add cost circuit breaker."}],"totalDurationMs":61574,"totalTokens":30560,"totalToolUseCount":10,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1699,"cache_read_input_tokens":28630,"output_tokens":230,"server_tool_use":{"w